+Technical Specification (TS) – Casual Puzzle Game App
+1. Project Overview
+
+The Casual Puzzle Game app is a mobile game designed for quick and entertaining gameplay. The game focuses on solving puzzles, matching elements, or completing levels with increasing difficulty.
+The goal is to provide a fun, addictive experience with smooth controls, progressive challenges, and optional social features.
+
+2. Functional Requirements
+2.1 Gameplay Mechanics
+
+Players interact with game elements by tapping, swiping, or dragging.
+
+Game modes:
+
+Level-based puzzles: Complete tasks to unlock the next level.
+
+Endless mode: Play as long as possible for a high score.
+
+Scoring system:
+
+Points for completing levels or combos.
+
+Bonuses for speed, accuracy, or streaks.
+
+Level difficulty increases progressively.
+
+2.2 Levels & Challenges
+
+Include at least 50 levels for initial release.
+
+Each level can have:
+
+Time limit or move limit
+
+Obstacles or special tiles
+
+Goals (e.g., clear all tiles, match 3 colors)
+
+Optional: daily or weekly challenge levels.
+
+2.3 Rewards & Progression
+
+Players earn coins, stars, or points for completing levels.
+
+Unlockable items, themes, or power-ups.
+
+Track player progress:
+
+Levels completed
+
+High scores
+
+Achievements
+
+2.4 User Interface
+
+Main menu with options:
+
+Play
+
+Levels selection
+
+Shop / Power-ups
+
+Settings
+
+In-game UI:
+
+Score counter
+
+Timer or moves remaining
+
+Pause button
+
+End-of-level summary screen with score, rewards, and option to replay.
+
+2.5 Social Features (Optional)
+
+Leaderboards to compare scores with friends or global players.
+
+Share achievements on social media.
+
+Invite friends to challenge levels.
+
+2.6 Settings
+
+Music and sound effects on/off.
+
+Notifications on/off.
+
+Language selection.
+
+Optional: difficulty adjustment.
+
+3. Non-Functional Requirements
+3.1 Platform
+
+Mobile: iOS and Android (cross-platform recommended)
+
+Optional web version
+
+3.2 Performance
+
+Smooth animations at 60 FPS.
+
+Responsive touch controls.
+
+Levels should load in <1 second.
+
+3.3 Data Storage
+
+Save game progress locally (SQLite, Realm, or device storage).
+
+Optional cloud save for cross-device sync.
+
+3.4 Security
+
+Protect user progress and in-game purchases.
+
+Optional user authentication for social features.
+
+3.5 Usability
+
+Intuitive tutorial for first-time players.
+
+Easy-to-read visual elements and feedback for player actions.
+
+4. Technical Stack
+Mobile
+
+Framework: Unity (C#) or Godot (GDScript/C#)
+
+Local storage: SQLite or PlayerPrefs (Unity)
+
+In-app purchases: platform-native (App Store, Google Play)
+
+Analytics: optional (Firebase or Unity Analytics)
+
+Web (Optional)
+
+HTML5 + Phaser.js or WebGL
+
+Backend: Node.js / Firebase for leaderboards
+
+Database: Firebase Realtime DB or MongoDB
+
+5. Future Enhancements
+
+Multiplayer mode for head-to-head challenges.
+
+Seasonal or themed levels.
+
+More complex power-ups and obstacles.
+
+In-game events and rewards.
+
+AI-powered hints or level suggestions.
+```
